---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'quick-verdict', text: 'Quick Verdict', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Side-by-Side Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'cigna-global', text: 'Cigna Global', level: 2 },
  { id: 'allianz-care', text: 'Allianz Care', level: 2 },
  { id: 'axa-global', text: 'AXA Global', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pricing', text: 'Pricing Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'latam-considerations', text: 'Latin America Considerations', level: 2 },
  { id: 'best-for', text: 'Which Is Best For You?', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'FAQs', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Allianz Care Review', href: '/providers/allianz-care' },
  { title: 'AXA Global Review', href: '/providers/axa-global' },
  { title: 'Mexico Insurance', href: '/countries/mexico/insurance' },
  { title: 'Costa Rica Insurance', href: '/countries/costa-rica/insurance' },
];

const mainComparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'feature', header: 'Feature' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Global' },
  { key: 'allianz', header: 'Allianz Care' },
  { key: 'axa', header: 'AXA Global' },
];

const mainComparisonRows = [
  { feature: 'Latin America Network', cigna: 'Excellent', allianz: 'Very Good', axa: 'Good' },
  { feature: 'Coverage Limit', cigna: 'Unlimited', allianz: '€1M - €3M', axa: '€3M' },
  { feature: 'Direct Billing', cigna: 'Extensive', allianz: 'Good', axa: 'Limited' },
  { feature: 'Mexico Network', cigna: 'Excellent', allianz: 'Very Good', axa: 'Good' },
  { feature: 'Brazil Network', cigna: 'Very Good', allianz: 'Good', axa: 'Limited' },
  { feature: 'Spanish Support', cigna: 'Excellent', allianz: 'Good', axa: 'Good' },
  { feature: 'US Evacuation', cigna: 'Included', allianz: 'Included', axa: 'Included' },
  { feature: 'Best For', cigna: 'Overall choice', allianz: 'Value seekers', axa: 'Budget option' },
];

const pricingColumns = [
  { key: 'profile', header: 'Profile' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Global' },
  { key: 'allianz', header: 'Allianz Care' },
  { key: 'axa', header: 'AXA Global' },
];

const pricingRows = [
  { profile: 'Single, Age 35', cigna: '$220-380/mo', allianz: '$180-280/mo', axa: '$160-250/mo' },
  { profile: 'Single, Age 45', cigna: '$320-480/mo', allianz: '$250-380/mo', axa: '$220-340/mo' },
  { profile: 'Couple, Age 40', cigna: '$520-780/mo', allianz: '$420-620/mo', axa: '$380-560/mo' },
  { profile: 'Family of 4', cigna: '$750-1,100/mo', allianz: '$600-900/mo', axa: '$520-780/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Cigna vs Allianz vs AXA: Best Insurance for Latin America Expats 2026"
  description="Compare the top insurers for expats in Latin America: Cigna Global, Allianz Care, and AXA Global. Coverage, networks, and pricing for Mexico, Costa Rica, Panama, and more."
  headline="Cigna vs Allianz vs AXA: Latin America Expat Insurance Compared"
  subheadline="Three premium insurers with strong Latin America presence. From Mexico to Argentina—here's how they compare."
  heroImage="/images/pages/provider-card-generic.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get Quotes"
  ctaButtonHref="/get-quotes"
>
  <h2 id="quick-verdict">Quick Verdict</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-6">
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border-2 border-primary-300 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-primary-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Best Overall</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Cigna Global</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">Largest network in Latin America. Best direct billing. Excellent Spanish-language support.</p>
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-300 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-green-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Best Value</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Allianz Care</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">Strong coverage at 15-20% less than Cigna. Good network across major markets.</p>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-amber-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Budget Option</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">AXA Global</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">Lowest prices but smaller network. Works well in Mexico and major cities.</p>
      <a href="/go/axa-global" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-amber-600 hover:bg-amber-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get AXA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p>
    Latin America has excellent private healthcare at lower costs than the US or Europe—but you need insurance that works with local hospitals. Cigna has the deepest network and best direct billing. Allianz offers great value. AXA is the budget choice with some network limitations.
  </p>

  <h2 id="comparison-table">Side-by-Side Comparison</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={mainComparisonColumns} rows={mainComparisonRows} />
  </div>

  <h2 id="cigna-global">Cigna Global</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Best Network</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Spanish Support</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Direct Billing</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    Cigna Global dominates in Latin America with the largest provider network and best direct billing relationships. They have dedicated Spanish-language customer service and long-standing partnerships with top hospitals across Mexico, Costa Rica, Panama, Colombia, and beyond.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Largest network across Latin America</li>
    <li>Best direct billing—less out-of-pocket</li>
    <li>24/7 Spanish-language support</li>
    <li>Strong presence in Mexico, Costa Rica, Panama</li>
    <li>Easy US evacuation for serious cases</li>
    <li>Best app and digital experience</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Most expensive option</li>
    <li>Premium pricing may be overkill for LATAM costs</li>
    <li>Some smaller countries have limited direct billing</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Expats who want the best service and don't want to deal with reimbursement hassles. Those living in Mexico or Central America where Cigna's network is strongest.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block bg-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/cigna-global" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <h2 id="allianz-care">Allianz Care</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Best Value</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Good Network</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Mental Health</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    Allianz Care offers comprehensive coverage at 15-20% less than Cigna. The network is slightly smaller but covers all major markets well. A smart choice for expats who want real coverage without paying premium prices.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>15-20% cheaper than Cigna</li>
    <li>Good network in Mexico, Costa Rica, Panama</li>
    <li>Strong mental health coverage</li>
    <li>Pre-existing conditions handled flexibly</li>
    <li>Moratorium underwriting option</li>
    <li>Backed by major European insurer</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Smaller direct billing network</li>
    <li>More reimbursement claims needed</li>
    <li>App less polished than Cigna</li>
    <li>Weaker in Brazil and Argentina</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Value-conscious expats who want comprehensive coverage. Those with pre-existing conditions. People comfortable with occasional reimbursement claims.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/allianz-care" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <h2 id="axa-global">AXA Global</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-amber-100 text-amber-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Budget Option</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-amber-100 text-amber-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Good in Mexico</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-amber-100 text-amber-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">French Insurer</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    AXA Global is the budget choice for Latin America. Coverage is comprehensive, but the direct billing network is smaller—expect more reimbursement claims. Works well in Mexico and major cities elsewhere, but may be limiting in smaller markets.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Lowest prices of the three</li>
    <li>Good coverage in Mexico</li>
    <li>Comprehensive benefits included</li>
    <li>Strong for families</li>
    <li>Good mental health benefits</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Smallest direct billing network</li>
    <li>More reimbursement hassles</li>
    <li>Limited presence in smaller countries</li>
    <li>€3M limit vs Cigna's unlimited</li>
    <li>Less Spanish support availability</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Budget-conscious expats in Mexico or major Latin American cities. Those comfortable managing reimbursement claims. Families looking for value.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/axa-global" class="inline-block bg-amber-600 hover:bg-amber-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get AXA Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/axa-global" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare All Three"
    description="Get personalized quotes from Cigna, Allianz, and AXA for your Latin America destination."
    buttonText="Get Free Quotes"
    buttonHref="/get-quotes"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="pricing">Pricing Comparison</h2>

  <p>
    Latin America coverage generally costs less than Asia or Europe because healthcare costs are lower. Cigna commands a premium for its network; Allianz offers solid value; AXA is the budget pick.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={pricingColumns} rows={pricingRows} />
  </div>

  <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500">
    *Estimated ranges for Latin America coverage excluding US. Prices vary based on age, health, and specific country of residence.
  </p>

  <h2 id="latam-considerations">Latin America Specific Considerations</h2>

  <h3>Healthcare Quality by Country</h3>
  <p>
    Private healthcare quality varies significantly across Latin America. Mexico, Costa Rica, and Panama have excellent private hospitals. Brazil has world-class care in major cities. Smaller countries may require evacuation for complex procedures.
  </p>

  <h3>Mexico</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna:</strong> Excellent—best direct billing at Hospital Angeles, ABC, Médica Sur</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz:</strong> Very good coverage at major private hospitals</li>
    <li><strong>AXA:</strong> Good network in Mexico City, Guadalajara, Monterrey</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Costa Rica</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna:</strong> Strong at CIMA, Clinica Biblica, Hospital Metropolitano</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz:</strong> Good coverage at main private hospitals</li>
    <li><strong>AXA:</strong> More limited direct billing</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Panama</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna:</strong> Excellent at Hospital Punta Pacifica, Pacifica Salud</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz:</strong> Good coverage in Panama City</li>
    <li><strong>AXA:</strong> Limited direct billing options</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Colombia</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna:</strong> Good network in Bogotá, Medellín, Cartagena</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz:</strong> Adequate coverage at major hospitals</li>
    <li><strong>AXA:</strong> Limited presence</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>US Evacuation</h3>
  <p>
    All three include medical evacuation to the US for conditions that can't be treated locally. This is crucial in Latin America—some complex surgeries or treatments may require US facilities. Cigna and Allianz have faster evacuation coordination.
  </p>

  <h2 id="best-for">Which Is Best For You?</h2>

  <div class="space-y-4 my-8">
    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose Cigna Global if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Want the largest network and best direct billing</li>
        <li>Live in Mexico or Central America</li>
        <li>Value Spanish-language support</li>
        <li>Prefer to avoid reimbursement claims</li>
        <li>Want the best digital experience</li>
        <li>Can afford premium pricing</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose Allianz Care if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Want comprehensive coverage at better prices</li>
        <li>Have pre-existing conditions</li>
        <li>Value mental health coverage</li>
        <li>Are comfortable with occasional reimbursement</li>
        <li>Live in major cities where network is solid</li>
        <li>Want good value without sacrificing coverage</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose AXA Global if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Are on a tight budget</li>
        <li>Live in Mexico where AXA's network is adequate</li>
        <li>Are comfortable managing reimbursement claims</li>
        <li>Have a family and need to manage costs</li>
        <li>Don't mind a smaller direct billing network</li>
        <li>€3M coverage limit is sufficient for your needs</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <h3>Is international insurance necessary in Latin America?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes, for private healthcare access. Public healthcare varies in quality and often has long waits. International insurance guarantees access to the best private hospitals. Plus, evacuation coverage is important for serious conditions.
  </p>

  <h3>Can I use local Mexican insurance instead?</h3>
  <p>
    Local insurance can work for Mexico-only coverage and is often cheaper. But it won't cover you if you travel, may not include evacuation, and typically has lower limits. International insurance makes sense if you travel or want broader protection.
  </p>

  <h3>What about dental and vision in Latin America?</h3>
  <p>
    Dental care is excellent and affordable in Latin America—many expats pay out of pocket. International plans typically include emergency dental only. Vision is similar. Consider local providers for routine dental/vision care.
  </p>

  <h3>Do I need US coverage if living in Latin America?</h3>
  <p>
    Including US coverage significantly increases premiums. If you're not spending time in the US, exclude it and save money. Emergency evacuation to the US is still included—you just wouldn't be covered for routine US care.
  </p>

  <h3>Which insurer processes claims fastest in Latin America?</h3>
  <p>
    Cigna is fastest due to extensive direct billing—you often don't need to file claims at all. For reimbursement claims, Cigna and Allianz are similar (1-2 weeks). AXA can be slower (2-3 weeks).
  </p>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This comparison is for informational purposes only. Prices and coverage details change. We are not insurance brokers. Verify current information directly with each provider before purchasing.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
